						<summary>

						<p>This is dated in the 36th year of Parākēsarivarman and is engraved in the <hi rend="italic">Vaṭṭeḻuttu</hi> alphabet. It is much damaged and is also incomplete. It seems to register some endowment for the daily supply of ghee for a lamp in the temple of Tirunaḍuvūr-Bhaṭārar at <hi rend="bold">Arikēsarinallūr</hi> a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Aḷa-nāḍu by one <hi rend="bold">Tiruchchēdi Irāsaḍi</hi> on behalf of his son <hi rend="bold">Irāsaḍi Śōlai.</hi> This is surmised to belong to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi> on account of the high regnal year given for the king.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
